UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellee, v. Juan ORNELAS, a.k.a. Juan Salazar, Defendant-Appellant. No. 08-13826

Non-Argument Calendar.

United States Court of Appeals, Eleventh Circuit. Feb. 18, 2009. Kristen Gartman Rogers, Federal Public Defender, SAL-Federal Public Defender, Mobile, AL, for Defendant-Appellant. Steven E. Butler, Mobile, AL, for Plaintiff-Appellee. *231Before BLACK, BARKETT and KRAVITCH, Circuit Judges. PER CURIAM:

Kristen Rogers, appointed counsel for Juan Ornelas in this direct criminal appeal, has moved to withdraw from further representation of the appellant and filed a brief pursuant to Anders v. California, 386 U.S. 738, 87 S.Ct. 1396, 18 L.Ed.2d 493 (1967). Because independent examination of the entire record reveals no arguable issues of merit, counsel’s motion to withdraw is GRANTED, and Ornelas’s conviction and sentence are AFFIRMED.
